In addition to the basic features such as reminders and calendar views, you can enable more options on the tab bar and use Pomo timer, habit and many more great features to help you become more productive.

- Pomo timer: Stay focused on your tasks and accomplish more.
- Habit: Build some good habits and get rid of the bad ones.

You can enable/disable them at any time via Settings > Tab Bar.

Time management doesn\'t have to be so complicated. If you don\'t know where to begin with, check out the articles below that we prepared for you. Hopefully, they can inspire you a little.\n\nFeel free to review them in the Help Center at any time.
Learn more tricks about time management

Get easy access to tasks by adding widgets to your homescreen.\n\nThere are various sizes and types of widget available on different platforms. Choose one that you like the most and begin to manage tasks more convenience.

Need a smarter Smart List in TickTick? Why not customizing your own smart list with personalized filters?\n\nFor example, you can combine filters \"3 day\", \"AND\", \"high priority\" to focus on what really matters in a short term. Or, combining filters \"today\", \"OR\" ,\"high priority\" to focus on both today\'s tasks and important tasks.

Users can manage a task easily by swiping it in task list. With TickTick premium, default swipe options can be changed with your own preferences.\n\nFor example, Short Swipe Left to change due date can be customized as to delete a task. You may also disable some of the options to avoid swiping by mistake.
Display your one-day tasks on a timeline. Be more focused and specific about your everyday plans.

When you are planning for a big project, sub-tasks might not be enough for you.\n\nFor example, a task named \"Product Branding\" and you are only responsible for market research. With the task description function, you may add some key description underneath the task along with all the sub-tasks.

You can set up estimated pomo for tasks and predict the expend time of each task. For example, \"Prepare for Honeymoon trip\" may be estimated as 9 pomo needed. \"Monthly report\" may be estimated as 5 pomo needed. So that you could adjust your schedules according to the amount of estimated pomo, or better understand your work efficiency by comparing estimated pomo with the actual pomo you gain.
